    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-11-27T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-11-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="633"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d633">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">762.94/213½</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Under Secretary of State</hi> (<hi
                        rend="italic">Welles</hi>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-11-27">November 27,
                            1937</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I inquired of the British Ambassador this morning when he called upon me whether
                    he had as yet any information from his Government <pb facs="0629" n="617"
                        xml:id="pg_617"/> in response to the inquiry addressed to him by the
                    Secretary of State in a conversation a few days ago as to whether the British
                    Government was informed of the nature and extent of any secret agreements which
                    might have been reached between Japan, Germany and Italy.</p>
                <p>The Ambassador pulled out of his pocket the attached “most secret”
                        memorandum<note n="22" xml:id="d633fn22">
                        <hi rend="italic">Infra</hi>.</note> which he said he had received on
                    Thursday and which he stated was the reply to the inquiry which he had addressed
                    to his Government after receiving the inquiry made by the Secretary of
                    State.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
